==Similar designs==
The flag of Somalia is similar in layout to a few other flags in terms of its combination of a single five-pointed star superimposed on a plain-colored background. However, it is not a derivative of, and was conceived independently and holds a different meaning from, these other designs.

The comparable [[flag of Vietnam]] features a yellow star set against a red backdrop. Similarly, the flag of the former [[Congo Free State]] and its successor the [[Belgian Congo]] have a yellow star affixed onto a dark blue field. The [[Bonnie Blue Flag]] of [[West Florida]] is perhaps the closest in design, as it also features a white star superimposed on a blue background; however, the star here is slightly larger and the blue field is navy in hue.

